@startuml Actor Scenarios
!define TITLE User Journeys & Actor Scenarios
title TITLE

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #E8F4F8
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #0066CC
}

== TENANT JOURNEY ==

actor Tenant as T

T -> T: 1. Download App
T -> T: 2. Sign Up / Login
T -> T: 3. Enable Location Services
T -> T: 4. Search Rooms\n(by city, date, budget)
T -> T: 5. View Room Details\n(photos, amenities, reviews)
T -> T: 6. Select Dates\n& confirm booking
T -> T: 7. Make Payment
T -> T: 8. Receive Confirmation Email
T -> T: 9. Check-in on Booking Date
T -> T: 10. Submit Maintenance\n(if needed)
T -> T: 11. Rate & Review Property
T -> T: 12. Check-out & Settle
T -> T: 13. View Invoice & History

== LANDLORD JOURNEY ==

actor Landlord as L

L -> L: 1. Sign Up as Landlord
L -> L: 2. Complete KYC/Verification
L -> L: 3. Add Property Details
L -> L: 4. Add Rooms\n(photos, amenities, rules)
L -> L: 5. Set Pricing & Availability
L -> L: 6. Receive Booking Notifications
L -> L: 7. Manage Bookings\n& Tenants
L -> L: 8. Respond to Maintenance\nRequests
L -> L: 9. View Tenant Reviews
L -> L: 10. Track Revenue\n& Payments
L -> L: 11. Download Invoices
L -> L: 12. View Analytics\n(occupancy, ratings)

== ADMIN JOURNEY ==

actor Admin as A

A -> A: 1. Login to Admin Dashboard
A -> A: 2. Manage Users\n(tenants, landlords)
A -> A: 3. Moderate Content\n(reviews, listings)
A -> A: 4. Resolve Disputes
A -> A: 5. Handle Complaints
A -> A: 6. Suspend/Ban Users
A -> A: 7. Monitor System Health
A -> A: 8. View System Analytics
A -> A: 9. Generate Reports
A -> A: 10. Manage Support Tickets

@enduml